:orange_heart:*Please take a moment to review our Code of Conduct*:orange_heart:

We want the HubSpot Developer community to be inclusive and welcoming. By following our Code of Conduct, you can help ensure that's the case.

TL;DR:
• Be respectful
• Be inclusive (try not to say, "Hey guys, hey boys, hey [any specific group]")
• No self promotion, except for <#C0121KGC6RM|showcase> and <#CBNDYJJAZ|jobs> 
• No unsolicited DMs
Read the <https://developers.HubSpot.com/slack/code-of-conduct|whole thing here> - and thanks for being a part of the HubSpot Developer Community!

Want to report.a violation? DM <@UQNEXHW14> or fill out the <https://form.asana.com/?k=p7aM0fpd3G4JGETDL_nYXg&d=8587152060687|anonymous form here>.
In the contact list filters for forms, can you only select landing pages for the page location, it looks like?

Hi, I have 11 domains on 1 enterprise portal. 9 are wordpress websites and 2 are magento websites. There are numerous contact form 7 (non-HubSpot form) on wordpress websites and all the data is coming into the single account. What would be the best way to segregate the contacts so that we can figure out the origin website and form name of the contact? We also want to know if a contact has submitted forms on multiple websites?
Hi, we have an CMS Enterprise client using Cloudflare. Is it possible to prevent HubSpot from using Cloudflare so they can use their own? It is hurting SEO.
